                  <textLang mainLang="en">English</textLang>
                  <msItem>
                     <p>Award by Dr Hugh Weston, Dr William Cliff, and Mr William Grinestede, in arbitration between the dean and chapter of <orgName key="org_101005">Christ Church, Oxford</orgName>, and John Thorneton, vicar of Leeds, concerning £10 annual pension from the church of <placeName key="place_103253">Leeds</placeName>, parcel of the possessions of the dissolved <orgName key="org_103019">priory of Holy Trinity, York</orgName>, granted by Henry VIII to Christ Church on 11 Dec. 1546. John to pay the pension from henceforth with arrears of £16. Dated <origDate when="1553-11-24">24 Nov. 1 Mary [1553]</origDate>. 
                        
                        </p>
                  </msItem>
